column8: Cloudy. Very high (95%) chance of rain. The chance of a thunderstorm. Light winds.

Cloudy. Very high (95%) chance of rain, most likely in the morning and afternoon. The chance of a thunderstorm, possibly severe with damaging winds and large hail in the afternoon and early evening. Heavy falls possible in the north. Winds north to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h tending west to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the late afternoon then becoming light in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 10 and 13 with daytime temperatures reaching between 15 and 21.

The chance of morning fog. Partly cloudy day. Medium (60%) chance of showers in the east, slight (20%) chance elsewhere. Snow possible above 1700 metres. The chance of a thunderstorm in the east in the early morning. Light winds becoming southeast to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching between 13 and 21.

Patchy morning fog near the New South Wales border. Partly cloudy day. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h becoming light during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 3 and 6 with daytime temperatures reaching between 15 and 21.
Patchy morning fog in the north. Partly cloudy day. Light winds. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 8 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 23.
